<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=cloen&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Cloen (cloen) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:cloen@hotmail.com" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to Cloen.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ok.  We all know how many people whine about harm touch.  And we all know that everyone who plays a Shadowknight wants to see it changed so that it is better.  But face it; harmtouch will not be changed.  So why doesn't everyone figure out what is good about it and use it for that.  I'd like to see comments on here about how SKs kick butt even without harmtouch or how harmtouch has worked well.  I'd personally play one even if we didn't have harmtouch at all.  So I see harm touch as an extra kick-butt attack.  One experience I've had is in highhold when I was level 20.  I was camping the named Gnoll for a couple hours and some level 38 warior came along to take it.  I got worried but didn't lose hope.   I thought about fearing etc but thought that I might just pull some nasty train or send it to a guard.  So when it finially spawned I cast darkness, sent my pet on it and started beating.  I waited until it was at about half life then Harm touched (He thought I was just another warrior.  lol.  I alwalys have /rol on)  The harmtouch took a quarter life off it and I was well on my way to getting the kill.  He was pissed that a green con got the kill from him.  So at that moment I was very pleased with my harmtouch.  I have also used it countless times to taunt and enimy off a friend.  I've used it in duels and it rocks.  It has a casting time of 0 which rocks!  It is one of the best DD spells and casting time of 0.  Wouldn't that be unbalanced if we could use it more than once every game day?  I know this message board is going to get filled with a million idiots saying how HT sucks but I'd prefer not to hear from you.  Ok here is an example of why increasing the damage on ht would be the dumbest thing they could do.  If the damage was increased that would mean a SK could instantly kill any caster at the same level.  And if it was the same as a paladins LH than it could just about get any class!  Now that would be unbalanced!  I think we can use it enough (about every hour and a half)  It kicks butt even in the 30's so it would be unfair to use it more than that.  I think it's annoying that people want it upgraded just so they can solo yellows.  The vamperic idea everyone says isn't horrible but can't you already see SKs are as good as any onther class in their own way.  Who cares if HT isn't as powerful as LH.  Shadow Knights ARE just as powerful as paladins.  If HT was upgraded then wouldn't you have to argue that rangers need something equally as powerful.  That's just lame.  Rangers have their own abilities just like SKs and Pallys.  So lets hear all those good stories about HT which are rarely heard because usually only the mad people post on here.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
