<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Cloen, my hat is off to you mate.  And here's why.  Because all of those sorry saps who whine and complain and hurl insults at Verant are missing the point.  You had FUN.  How gratifying was it to keep control of the kill on that mob ?  Im sure that you had a grin from ear to ear and were laughing your balls off bro.  Good Game.<p>

All those numbers that everyone posted are worthless.  SK were not designed to be masters of damage.  Their HT was not intended to put them on par with a monk or Rogue.  Why would you think that ?  SK planar armor has the same AC as Paladins, so they are tied for the second highest.  They can heal themselves whilst still damaging the enemy.  Dot's that debuff the enemy.  Pet, pet and did i mention that they have a pet ?<p>

SK are TANKS.  They are not casters, they are not healers.  THey are the masters though at just being plain badass.  Feign death ?  are you kidding me ?  how damned good is that spell ?  pulling, clearing agro in a fight.....wow.<p>

You might think that this post had nothing to do with HT, but it does.  I will side with Verant on this issue for the first time in my life.  Balance.  Have any of you ever seen an SK with a cloak of flames and a YK outdamage a warrior ?  I have.  Have any of you ever camped the fishbone earing ?  My SK stole that kill before the guy even spawned. ZERO cast time.  What about the Ancient Cyclops ?  KSed again.  Did you guys see me duel that enchanter ?  oh yeah, i harmed him down so fast, resisted so many of his spells and his pet couldnt do shit to me cause of my AC and the fact that his sword and shield was fleeing in terror that the duel ended in under a minute...and he certainly didnt flee due to him being snared.<p>

If anyone would like to try to pull the plane of hate or fear with a warrior or a paladin, by all means, get the group killed.  BUt frankly, if you ever want something accomplished, call in your local SK and get the job done, because THAT ladies and gentleman , is where the true beauty of an SK becomes readily apparent.<p>

TO all of you who disagreed with CLoen, children, open your eyes.  Dont be so damned narrow minded about the HT.  No shit you dont do damage to a mob that has 4k + hitpoints.  WHy are you so surprised ?  it's just simple mathematics as some joker pointed out earlier.<p>

You will flame me im sure for not stating my name, but i will tell you this.  I have played all three tank classes.  War, SK and Pally, and far and away the most versatile was the SK.  very simple.  this game is about adaptation and accessability.  Bread and butter of the Sk class.<p>

Your's truly,<p>

