<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Cloen, I would just like to say that it was nice to see someone try to have a good thing to say about Harm Touch and the Shadow Knight.  I was just sorry to have to read all the trash and flames to find the true stories you asked for.  <p>

The more I read these boards, the more I come to believe that the Shadow Knight is not for the average player.  The spells and skills available to you provide for some interesting tatical posibilities.  If people would quit trying to kill with harm touch and explore these posibilities, there would be more good stories for you to read.  (Note: Harm Touch is not the defining skill of the Shadow Knight, it is only one skill.)<p>

Anyway, here are a couple of stories.<p>

Being a level 34 Shadow Knight and wanting the Darkforge armor I spend some time in Cazic camping the Crusaders.  The group I was in was in the middle of a group change and somehow only 3 of us ended up in Upper Tae when a Judicator spawned.  I quick kill was desired so the caster started dropping the DDs and promptly started getting attacked.  A couple lucky hits with my sword and a full damage harm touch and it was on me allowing the caster to get off that all critical heal stopping DD.  We won the fight as additional spawns came up and party members started to arrive.  I like to think that this was a case where 'harm touch' and not 'lay hands' was called for to save the day.<p>

Now I do not count on harm touch allowing me to slay things out of my range, but when a rare comes up and has one of those nice drops it can be very tempting to try.  Was in South Karana when the druid with the Bark Shield ran by while crossing the zone invis.  Was just too tempting and without thinking I started to cast the first of 2 dots.  Got the first to stick and decided to close and not waist time on the second.  Was taking a real beating but was trying to get her down into harm touch range.  Well it was getting close so I fired off the harm touch.  In this case it was not enough so I promply casted feign death.  I may have lost the fight, but I was able to give it a try and did not die.  Now you could say I should have one, but hey them Druids use fire and us trolls burn easy.<p>

I hope these stories are what you are looking for.<hr>Bluud Wyrmbait<br>
