<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I won't be reading this thread again, so flame me if you want....<p>

Harm touch is niiiice.  Rather than bitch about it not nuking as much damage (in proportion) look at its new useful side.  Breaking the lord spawn in lguk?  Got that wiz blasting away on you, NUKE HIS ASS!  I do 441 dmg at lvl 42 (lvl 41 and up you get more than 10 x lvl plus 1) 441 dmg is nice on a caster, period.  Also this business of resists....use HT wisely, and you won't have an issue with resists.  Don't open a fight with harm touch, you will likely get a partial resist.  Don't harm touch mob's that are very-red cons (unless you're about to die anyway).  It comes down to this....a lvl 40 wiz is nuking for like 380, i was nuking for 401, so for that 1 time in 90 minutes emergency situation, yeh, it rocks.  Would it be nice for them to up the dmg on HT in a non-pvp situation, yes, i'd dig it, and i'm all for it.  Will it happen?...No.  They've said no before, they've said no again, and i'm sure they'll say no in the future.  Do you NEED HT's power upped....if so you are doing something wrong.<p>

ALSO!! To the jackass who responded to the first post with an immature flame, just go away.  I've anti-ks'd with harm touch more times than i can count, and i could solo any gnoll in highpass by lvl 20.  To the guy that kept the warrior from snatching the named, saweet, fun to strut your stuff isn't it :)  .<p>

