<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I think there is a big problem with the understanding of a Shadow Knight.<br>
Almost everybody compares HT with LH and that is sooooo... wrong.<br>
I have to be honest I have little experience playing SKs and the first ten levels are quite dragging,<br>
but I have played Pallies to higher levels. <br>
Harm Touch is a life saver as well as LH and so far I was fighting all the stuff in Nektulos and <br>
HT saved my life I don't know how often. It is just a question when to use it.<br>
I allways use it in the (almost) last moment (when my life hits 1 1/2 bubs) I HT the bear who is from<br>
dragged out fighting in his 50%s, after the HT he is either dead or so damaged that I can finish him off<br>
Once I also managed to run away (when the bear was close to death, but I could't finish him off) but the <br>
HT made him slow enough to not get even close to me.<br>
But HT is not the main best feature of an SK. <br>
1.I think the best features are DOING casting and serious mele damage and lifetap (heal)<br>
Any other hybrid class can pack and go home on that combo. <br>
2.You get a pet and just having a friend arround when a warrior and a pally gets lonely is cool.<br>
3.You have all the options with a SK and I had the greatest fun playing her.<br>
4.When ever you get into the "good" parts of norath people look at you with 10 times more respect than at a Pally.<br>
5.And its much easier to outsmart MOBs much easier than as a Smashin-Bashin-Warrior-type which makes it much more fun <br>
than just hitting one button and wait till that thing in front of you falls.<p>

Sorry for the little Excurse here, but once and for all if you don't like HT and SKs then play a stupid Warrior<br>
it might match your intelligence level.<hr>Terrora <br>
