<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am lvl 34, and I still find HT useful. I have recently been fighting a lot in Cazic, where there are lizzies that heal themselves, or worse, flee and THEN heal themselves while you are in hot pursuit.  <p>

When fighting a MOB who heals, once you whack them down to about one third HP,if you time it right you can HT them to death before they can heal again. (I have been in groups that have had to whack a MOB down to one third health three times or more!) Sure it's better if you have casters to nuke the MOB when it's low, bit sometimes you have no casters, they are OOM, or worse, they are being whacked on.  Then HT is a 340 point insta-nuke to finish off a pesky healing MOB.<p>

The other useful time is when a MOB is fleeing.  Say you've left your party to chase down the MOB so it doesn't retuen with friends.  You know your non-tanks are likely having to deal with other MOBs back at the pull spot, and you have to get back fast.  Worse, if you chase the fleeing MOB much farther, he's gonna find a buddy.  So harm touch him to death and get back to your group ASAP.<p>

HT can also be used as a maga-taunt, or it is handy as a last blast to finish a weakened MOB so you can get over and start taunting/tanking the MOB currently beating up your healer.<br>
  <br>
Yes - you can only do this once avery hour and a half, but HT is very handy to have when breaking a spawn or when several mobs show up uninvited and your group is stil in recovery mode.<hr>Falkko<br>
37th season Tier'Dal Shadowknight<br>
Wolves of Ragnarok<br>
The Rathe</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
