<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Verant in it's infinite wisdom, has nerfed the hybrid classes in order to make pure casters and melee'ers appealing. Its that simple. But in doing so, the SK's bore the larger brunt of the nerfing. To anyone who things Harm Touch is weak, your wrong! It is a powerful tool, but it must be used too sparingly as it's a once a day charge. If it can't be vamped to match the Pally's Lay Hands (And I don't think it should!) then it should at least be a once each HALF day charge. Why? Contrary to the opinion above where someone said we SK's are almost like warriors in our skills, we are NOT!!! We NEVER get duel wield, only get Double attack at 20 (5 levels past when warriors get it), I just heard we can NEVER get critical hits regardless of strength or level, and our spells that supposedly give us an edge are probably about the same as necro's half our level. Pet? Lame! No means a tank, but I agree on someone's comparison to it being a decent DoT with 'taunt off'. And unless we butcher our stats at creation, we do NOT have the hit points of warriors! This is because we have to make sure to annie up some of those extra points into intelligence so that our casting works well! Unless someone screws up creating a warrior, they will not concern themselves with beefing up that stat! And are you all aware that hybrid classes take an XP nerf? That's right! On a level to level comparison, SK's get less XP killing a MoB than non-hybrid classes. All that said, I'd take the nerfed SK over a warrior anyday, as the personality of an evil, anti-paladin, along with the lame, but still extra casting ability, as well as the lame pet and the once a day Harm Touch, all combine to quite a fun package to operate in an RPG! So while I do point out the pitfalls, I am aware of the advantages! And by the way, all the players I know in the upper (+40) levels, seem to all agree that they'd prefer having an SK over a Pally in their group anyday, because of the versatility the SK brings! So enjoy!<p>

All Hail Innorruk, Prince Of Hate!<hr>Draeghos Gowron<br>
DEF/SK<br>
Circle Of The Chosen<br>
Guild Officer</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
